 Matthew D. Hoffman, Monica Din-\n1665\tculescu, and Douglas Eck. 2019. Music Transformer: Generating Music with\n1666\tLong-Term Structure. In International Conference on Learning Representations\n1667\t(ICLR). arXiv:1809.04281.\n1668\t\n1669\t[14] Yujia Huang, Adishree Ghatare, Yuanzhe Liu, Ziniu Hu, Qinsheng Zhang, Chan-\n1670\tdramouli Shama Sastry, Siddharth Gururani, Sageev Oore, and Yisong Yue. 2024.\n1671\tSymbolic Music Generation with Non-Differentiable Rule Guided Diffusion. In\n1672\tProceedings of the 41st International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML) (Pro-\n1673\tceedings of Machine Learning Research, Vol. 235). PMLR, 19772–19797.\n1674\t\n1675\t[15] Yu-Siang Huang and Yi-Hsuan Yang. 2020. Pop Music Transformer: Beat-based\n1676\tModeling and Generation of Expressive Pop Piano Compositions. In Proceedings of\n1677\tthe 28th ACM International Conference on Multimedia (MM ’20). ACM, 1180–1188.\n1678\tdoi:10.1145/3394171.3413671\n1679\t\n1680\t[16] Wengong Jin, Kevin Yang, Regina Barzilay, and Tommi Jaakkola. 2019. Learning\n1681\tMultimodal Graph-to-Graph Translation for Molecular Optimization. In Interna-\n1682\ttional Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR).\n1683\t\n1684\t[17] Tsung-Yi Lin, Priya Goyal, Ross Girshick, Kaiming He, and Piotr Dollár. 2017. Fo-\n1685\tcal Loss for Dense Object Detection. In IEEE International Conference on Computer\n1686\tVision (ICCV). 2980–2988.\n1687\t\n1688\t[18] Peiling Lu, Xin Xu, Chenfei Kang, Botao Yu, Chengyi Xing, Xu Tan, and Jiang\n1689\tBian. 2023. MuseCoco: Generating Symbolic Music from Text. arXiv preprint\n1690\tarXiv:2306.00110 (2023).\n1691\t\n1692\t[19] Ang Lv, Xu Tan, Peiling Lu, Wei Ye, Shikun Zhang, Jiang Bian, and Rui Yan. 2023.\n1693\tGETMusic: Generating Any Music Tracks with a Unified Representation and\n1694\tDiffusion Framework. arXiv preprint arXiv:2305.10841 (2023).\n1695\t\n1696\t[20] Jonathan Mallinson, Aliaksei Severyn, Eric Malmi, and Guillermo Garrido. 2020.\n1697\tFELIX: Flexible Text Editing Through Tagging and Insertion. In Findings of the\n1698\tAssociation for Computational Linguistics: EMNLP 2020. Association for Computa-\n1699\ttional Linguistics, 1244–1255.\n1700\t\n1701\t[21] Eric Malmi, Sebastian Krause, Sascha Rothe, Daniil Mirylenka, and Aliaksei\n1702\tSeveryn. 2019. Encode, Tag, Realize: High-Precision Text Editing. In Proceedings\n1703\tof the 2019 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing and\n1704\tthe 9th International Joint Conference on Natural Language Processing (EMNLP-\n1705\tIJCNLP). Association for Computational Linguistics, 5054–5065.\n1706\t\n1707\t[22] Chenlin Meng, Yutong He, Yang Song, Jiaming Song, Jiajun Wu, Jun-Yan Zhu, and\n1708\tStefano Ermon. 2022. SDEdit: Guided Image Synthesis and Editing with Stochastic\n1709\tDifferential Equations. In International Conference on Learning Representations\n1710\t(ICLR).\n1711\t\n1712\t[23] Lejun Min, Junyan Jiang, Gus Xia, and Jingwei Zhao. 2023. Polyffusion: A\n1713\tDiffusion Model for Polyphonic Score Generation with Internal and External\n1714\tControls. In Proceedings of the 24th International Society for Music Information\n1715\tRetrieval Conference (ISMIR). 231–238.\n1716\t\n1717\t[24] Kostiantyn Omelianchuk, Vitaliy Atrasevych, Artem Chernodub, and Oleksandr\n1718\tSkurzhanskyi. 2020. GECToR – Grammatical Error Correction: Tag, Not Rewrite.\n1719\tIn Proceedings of the Fifteenth Workshop on Innovative Use of NLP for Building\n1720\tEducational Applications (BEA 2020). Association for Computational Linguistics,\n1721\t163–170.\n1722\t\n1723\t[25] Sageev Oore, Ian Simon, Sander Dieleman, Douglas Eck, and Karen Simonyan.\n1724\t2020. This Time with Feeling: Learning Expressive Musical Performance. Neural\n1725\t\n1726\t\fBeatEdit: Symbolic Music Generation as Explicit Editing\n1727\t\n1728\tACM MM ’26, November 10–14, 2026, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\n1729\t\n1730\tA Encoding Technical Specification\n1731\tA.1 Complete Token Vocabulary\n1732\t